The primary use case is building complex filter expressions using a fluent API.  For example:

```java
FilterExpressionBuilder b = new FilterExpressionBuilder();
Expression exp = b.and(b.eq("genre", "drama"), b.gte("year", 2020)).build();
```

This creates a filter equivalent to `genre == "drama" AND year >= 2020`. The builder supports various operators like `eq`, `gte`, `in`, `ne`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, and logical combinations (`and`, `or`, `not`).  Grouping is also supported for creating more complex nested filters.

