The `FilterExpressionBuilder` is used to programmatically construct filter expressions. Common examples include filtering by equality (`eq`), inequality (`ne`), greater than/less than (`gt`, `lt`), and checking if a value is within a set (`in`). Logical operators (`and`, `or`) can combine multiple conditions. The `group` method allows creating nested filter expressions. For example:

```java
FilterExpressionBuilder b = new FilterExpressionBuilder();
var exp = b.and(b.eq("genre", "drama"), b.gte("year", 2020));
```

