The primary use case is calculating the cosine similarity between two vectors:

```java
float[] vectorX = {0.1f, 0.2f, 0.3f};
float[] vectorY = {0.4f, 0.5f, 0.6f};
double similarity = EmbeddingMath.cosineSimilarity(vectorX, vectorY);
```

It can also be used to compute the dot product and norm of a vector:

```java
float[] vector = {1.0f, 2.0f, 3.0f};
float dotProduct = EmbeddingMath.dotProduct(vector, vector);
float norm = EmbeddingMath.norm(vector);
```

